The paper discusses program transformations and analysis techniques, which are typically studied in the programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-categories. The focus on control-flow refinement and the use of Horn clauses suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the application of the technique to termination and cost analysis suggests a connection to scientific computing (cs.SC).
